{{nihongo foot|'''''Ben Bero Beh'''''|べんべろべえ|Ben Bero Bē|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} is a [[Platform game|platform]] [[arcade game]] released by [[Taito Corporation|Taito]] in [[1984 in video gaming|1984]]. The player guides Dami-chan, a [[superhero]], through an [[Apartment|apartment complex]] which is on fire. Armed with a [[fire extinguisher]], Dami-chan must make his way down the levels avoiding [[gas explosion]]s, crumbling floors, damaged lighting fixtures, and various enemies that pop out of the doors. The goal is to extinguish the fire and rescue Dami-chan's girlfriend, Nao-chan.

Various characters and gameplay elements from the game would go on to appear in later games made by Taito, particularly ''[[Bubble Bobble]]''. The game would later appear on ''[[Taito Memories|Taito Memories II Jōkan]]'', and the game has since been ported to the [[Nintendo Switch]] and [[PlayStation 4]] as part of the [[Arcade Archives]].

== Gameplay ==
''Ben Bero Beh'' is a platform arcade game. The player controls a superhero, Dami-chan, though a series of apartment complexes that are on fire in order to save his girlfriend, Nao-chan.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Doolan|first=Liam|date=1 October 2020|title=Taito's 1984 Action Platform Game Ben Bero Beh Joins The Arcade Archives|url=https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2020/10/taitos_1984_action_platform_game_ben_bero_beh_joins_the_arcade_archives|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201006105123/https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2020/10/taitos_1984_action_platform_game_ben_bero_beh_joins_the_arcade_archives|archive-date=6 October 2020|access-date=13 October 2020|website=[[Nintendo Life]]|language=en-GB}}</ref> To get though the flaming building, Dami-chan is armed with a fire extinguisher that can put out said fires, as well as manipulate stage hazards in order to get through them.<ref name=":0" /> Dami-chan can also jump to avoid fall damage from collapsed floors, enemies that appear from time to time out of the apartment doors, and various other hazards.<ref name=":0" /> The quicker the player completes the level, the more bonus points the player gets after completing a level.<ref name=":0" />

Cameos of characters from various other Taito games also appear to try to halt Dami-chan's progress, such as the enemy spies from ''[[Elevator Action]]'', and Chack'n from ''[[Chack'n Pop]]''.<ref name=":0" />

== Release ==
Ben Bero Beh was released by Taito in Japan in November 1984.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Akagi|first=Masumi|url=https://archive.org/stream/ArcadeGameList1971-2005#page/n43/mode/1up|title=アーケードTVゲームリスト 国内•海外編 (1971-2005)|publisher=[[:ja:アミューズメント通信社|Amusement News Agency]]|year=2006|isbn=978-4990251215|edition=1st|pages=42}}</ref>

=== Conversions ===
The game never received any home ports until the release of ''[[Taito Memories|Taito Memories II Jōkan]]'', which featured the game via emulation''.''<ref name=":1">{{Cite magazine|date=30 September 2020|title=『べんべろべえ』を配信前に最速プレイ！ 『俺たちのアケアカ』本日（9月30日）20時00分より生放送【ファミ通チャンネル】|url=https://www.famitsu.com/news/202009/30206401.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019020741/https://www.famitsu.com/news/202009/30206401.html|archive-date=19 October 2020|access-date=31 October 2020|magazine=[[Famitsu]]|language=ja}}</ref> On October 1, 2020, [[Hamster Corporation]] released a port of the game to [[Nintendo Switch]] and [[PlayStation 4]] as part of their [[Arcade Archives|Arcade Archive]] initiative.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=アーケードアーカイブス べんべろべえ|url=https://www.4gamer.net/games/532/G053288/|access-date=31 October 2020|website=[[4Gamer.net]]|language=ja}}</ref> This port features various display options, new gameplay modes, and an online [[Score (game)|leaderboard]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" />

== Reception and legacy ==
''Ben Bero Beh'' enjoyed success in Japanese arcades. ''Game Machine'' listed ''Ben Bero Beh'' on their November 15, 1984 issue as being the fourth most-successful table arcade unit of the month.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Game Machine's Best Hit Games 25 - テーブル型TVゲーム機 (Table Videos)|magazine=[[:ja:ゲームマシン|Game Machine]]|issue=248|publisher=[[:ja:アミューズメント通信社|Amusement Press, Inc.]]|date=15 November 1984|page=25|lang=ja}}</ref>

